Finance Analyzer
Personal Financial Dashboard  ·  Python · Pandas · Matplotlib · Streamlit
github.com/ziadzakaryaai-ux/finance-analyzer

Project Overview
Finance Analyzer is an interactive web dashboard that turns raw transaction data into clear financial insights. Upload a CSV of your transactions and instantly see where your money goes, how your balance trends over time, which expenses are unusually high, and whether your savings rate is on track — all in a dark-themed UI built for clarity.

Built as a capstone project during a self-directed Python and data analysis learning path, progressing from pure Python scripts through Pandas and NumPy to a fully deployed Streamlit web application.

Features

 	Dynamic filtering
Filter all charts and metrics by month and category from the sidebar. Everything updates instantly with no page reload.

 	Summary metrics
Four headline cards showing total income, total expenses, net balance, and savings rate — color-coded green for healthy, red for negative.

 	Monthly income vs expenses
Side-by-side bar chart comparing income and spending for every month in the dataset.

 	Spending by category
Horizontal bar chart ranked from highest to lowest spend, highlighting your biggest cost category in red.

 	Net balance trend
Line chart showing monthly balance over time with green fill above zero and red fill below.

 	Outlier detection
Automatically flags statistically unusual transactions using mean + 1.8 standard deviations — no manual threshold needed.

 	3-month rolling average
Smoothed spending trend overlaid on monthly data to cut through short-term noise.

Tech Stack

Layer	Tool	Purpose
Data loading & cleaning	Pandas	read_csv, date parsing, groupby, resample
Numerical analysis	NumPy	Rolling averages, std deviation, outlier detection
Visualizations	Matplotlib	Bar, line, pie charts with custom dark theme
Web application	Streamlit	Interactive UI, file upload, sidebar filters
Deployment	Streamlit Cloud	Free hosting with public URL for portfolio

CSV Format
The app expects a CSV file with these five columns:

Column	Type	Example values
date	string	2024-01-15
type	string	income  or  expense
category	string	Food, Transport, Salary, Bills
description	string	Lunch at restaurant
amount	float	59.35

A sample file with 595 realistic transactions spanning all of 2024 is included in the repository.

Getting Started
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOURUSERNAME/finance-analyzer.git
cd finance-analyzer

2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the app
streamlit run app.py
The app opens at http://localhost:8501. Upload your transactions.csv from the sidebar.

Project Structure
File	Description
app.py	Main Streamlit application — all UI, charts, and analysis logic
transactions.csv	Sample dataset with 595 transactions across 2024
requirements.txt	Python dependencies (pandas, matplotlib, numpy, streamlit)
README.md	Project documentation

